Bank Rossiya Targets Bank Saint Petersburg, Kommersant Reports

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-09-14T04:26:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/bank-rossiya-targets-bank-saint-petersburg-kommersant-reports.html
OAO Bank Rossiya, controlled by
Yury Kovalchuk, is in talks to buy shares of Bank Saint
Petersburg from its largest shareholder, Alexander Savelyev,
with a view to taking control,  Kommersant  reported, citing an
unidentified person close to Bank Rossiya.  At present there is no controlling shareholder at Bank
Saint Petersburg and Savelyev wants to sell his 30 percent
stake, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 